name: Starlight

reviews.review_text: You should find this place while you are in goa. The food is tasty, and the service is warm. place gets crowded sometimes other than that it's a very comfortable place with a lot of options on seafood. It's far from all the hassle of beaches and cities. However, it's a great escape, the one you should always opt for

We reached Starlight close to shutting in the afternoon, and I'm glad we didn't miss out on a scrumptious late lunch. Butter Garlic Prawns and Mussels Rawa fry are highly recommended.  This was 2nd visit and definitely not my last. :)

Visited Starlight for lunch on Tuesday. Reached before 1 pm so we managed to get a table by the river side. Our server Bandhan was very polite and attentive to our order requests. The fans and music being played sort of made it difficult to have a decent conversation without having to literally sort of shout. We ordered the usual beverages. Then started off with some french fries which would have been better had they been lightly salted, we did ask for Bandhan to get some salt. Squids batter fry which was fresh and tasty. Lepo rawa fry these were sort of over done making the fish sort of hard. Crab xec xec was really good and spicy with a decent amount of small crabs for the price. Lastly we had the modso fish thali
which was the highlight of the meal. Fish nicely covered in rawa and fried properly. All in all a decent lunch outing

description:
**Restaurant Review: Starlight, Carmona**

Tucked away in the charming locale of Carmona, Starlight boasts an impressive rating of 4.2 stars from over 4,600 patrons, fueled by a love for its Goan cuisine, which highlights tags such as "seafood" (171 mentions), "river" (114 mentions), and delightful "thalis" (27 mentions). Guests rave about the tasty dishes served in a serene atmosphere—the perfect escape from the busy beaches that define Goa.

**Ambiance & Design**  
As patrons step into Starlight, they are greeted by an inviting décor that captures the essence of the coastal charm—earthy tones accented with vibrant tropical colors. The restaurant features a lovely riverside seating area, as evident from the customer-submitted photos showcasing a blend of rustic and contemporary elements that enhance the dining experience. Natural light floods the space during the day, complemented by gentle ambient music that sets a relaxed tone. However, some guests have noted that this atmosphere can be disrupted when the restaurant fills up, leading to a lively yet noisy environment that can make conversation a bit challenging.

![Riverside Seating Area](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdm6cjwh9ANEqlEnDt7lxkOhvKbsect_DbB3Typlq6QORhGELB0F-KQTszO-P7ZSp_uDbvp6UESyR_QwBA-Oj5NZ_V4vCxCZGSGw79ZLRDFOnSEVdZdBlAYFhDyvznsmnueu0PKQfQ=w375-h281-p)

**Menu & Culinary Experience**  
Starlight’s menu is a treasure trove of seafood delights. Signature dishes include the much-praised Butter Garlic Prawns and Mussels Rawa Fry, both of which promise an explosion of flavor, perfectly prepared to hallmark Goan cuisine. The highlight of many meals is undoubtedly the Fish Thali, a culinary masterpiece featuring fish coated in rava, fried to perfection—a favorite among repeat visitors. The presentation mirrors the culinary creativity, boasting colorful plate arrangements that are almost too beautiful to eat, as exemplified in the vibrant dishes shared in various customer photos. Vegetarian options are available, but the emphasis clearly shines on the rich offerings of fresh seafood.

![Fish Thali](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdnyZN51NdaZWCeeK0sPJmAvVqOqFOrfnlpKIPxp11JBit6yiVb3t-ksmvIeKa8beA1osoY8P9vppAUMhAK24gQC4_ydkNwG9UYVFaU81-FdLLpdk1ENdGYYv0KL8Wy0v154aVBPvw=w375-h281-p)

**Customer Experience & Service**  
Customer experiences at Starlight reflect a warm and attentive service style, with staff like Bandhan noted for their politeness and efficiency. The restaurant can get bustling, especially during peak hours, so it’s recommended to arrive early for a riverside table, or risk waiting for a spot within their cozy environment. While the general feedback leans towards positivity, some reviews indicate minor hiccups, such as food temperature consistency or seasoning.

![Seafood Platter](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdnHOG09G0Fsvp_IR2qE2eMdtUS-Y5v7GV5x1KBAJpV_4O_JCzpxVVCwGo7GJ-58ytCsL8gvcraog803NRs9rI_E4Yh9IFKUg7HTI5-AK8zD1_zKmmAQdYywwuFjKstHuj9cHCa8=w375-h281-p)

**Popularity & Reviews**  
Starlight has carved a niche for itself among locals and tourists alike, becoming a popular dining destination for those seeking authentic Goan flavours paired with a serene backdrop. Regulars often share their fondness for the extensive seafood options and the comforting atmosphere that promotes relaxation. Social media buzz around Starlight showcases beautiful food photography and testimonials celebrating its culinary successes, further elevating its reputation.

In conclusion, Starlight in Carmona is more than just a dining spot; it’s an experience that seamlessly blends good food, a picturesque setting by the river, and friendly service. For anyone seeking to indulge in delicious Goan seafood away from the usual hustle, Starlight invites you to discover flavors that are truly worth savoring.
